briefdescription.para: Gets or sets whether the calc engine should keep a cache with parsed expressions.
Gets or sets whether the calc engine should optimize expressions when they are parsed.
Gets or sets a string that specifies special characters that are valid for identifiers.

detaileddescription.para: Identifiers must start with a letter or an underscore, which may be followed by additional letters, underscores, or digits. This string allows you to specify additional valid characters such as ':' or '!' (used in Excel range references for example).

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the DataContext for this CalcEngine.

detaileddescription.para: Once a DataContext is set, all public properties of the object become available to the CalcEngine, including sub-properties such as "Address.Street". These may be used with expressions just like any other constant.

briefdescription.para: Gets the dictionary that contains function definitions.
Gets the dictionary that contains simple variables (not in the DataContext).
Gets or sets the CultureInfo to use when parsing numbers and dates.
Parses a string into an Expression.

simplesect.para: An Expression object that can be evaluated.

detaileddescription.para: If you are going to evaluate the same expression several times, it is more efficient to parse it only once using the Parse method and then using the Expression.Evaluate method to evaluate the parsed expression.

memberdef.argsstring: (string functionName, int parmMin, int parmMax, CalcEngineFunction fn)
memberdef.name: RegisterFunction

briefdescription.para: Registers a function that can be evaluated by this CalcEngine.
Registers a function that can be evaluated by this CalcEngine.
Gets an external object based on an identifier.

detaileddescription.para: This method is useful when the engine needs to create objects dynamically. For example, a spreadsheet calc engine would use this method to dynamically create cell range objects based on identifiers that cannot be enumerated at design time (such as "AB12", "A1:AB12", etc.)

briefdescription.para: CalcEngine parses strings and returns Expression objects that can be evaluated.

detaileddescription.para: This class has three extensibility points:
Use the DataContext property to add an object's properties to the engine scope.
Use the RegisterFunction method to define custom functions.
Override the GetExternalObject method to add arbitrary variables to the engine scope.
